{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KnqQdZCTj3zaE1ekzABoyg","type":"tool_result","content":"   250→\n   251→function openDrawer(workflowName, stepName) {\n   252→    var wf = workflowsData.find(function(w) { return w.name === workflowName; });\n   253→    if (!wf) return;\n   254→    var step = wf.steps.find(function(s) { return s.name === stepName; });\n   255→    if (!step) return;\n   256→\n   257→    document.getElementById('drawer-title').textContent = stepName;\n   258→    var body = '<dl class=\"run-meta\">';\n   259→    body += '<dt>Type</dt><dd>' + step.type + '</dd>';\n   260→    body += '<dt>Results</dt><dd>' + (step.results ? step.results.join(', ') : 'none') + '</dd>';\n   261→    if (step.config) {\n   262→        for (var k in step.config) {\n   263→            if (k === 'max_attempts' || k === 'prompt' || k === 'command' || k === 'script') {\n   264→                body += '<dt>' + k + '</dt><dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k] + '</dd>';\n   265→            }\n   266→        }\n   267→    }\n   268→    body += '</dl>';\n   269→    body += '<div id=\"drawer-content\"><p style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">Loading content...</p></div>';\n   270→\n   271→    document.getElementById('drawer-body').innerHTML = body;\n   272→    document.getElementById('step-drawer').classList.add('drawer-open');\n   273→\n   274→    fetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/workflows/' + encodeURIComponent(workflowName) + '/steps/' + encodeURIComponent(stepName) + '/content')\n   275→        .then(function(r) { if (r.ok) return r.text(); return ''; })\n   276→        .then(function(text) {\n   277→            var el = document.getElementById('drawer-content');\n   278→            if (text) {\n   279→                el.innerHTML = '<pre>' + text.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;') + '</pre>';\n   280→            } else {\n   281→                el.innerHTML = '<p style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">No content available</p>';\n   282→            }\n   283→        });\n   284→}\n   285→\n   286→function closeDrawer() {\n   287→    document.getElementById('step-drawer').classList.remove('drawer-open');\n   288→}\n   289→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01J4ny8RFKt7ajdut1mfrG1Y","session_id":"735f5643-f2ce-48be-a0fe-61ddf324c836","uuid":"c19715ea-de75-4f7f-9eb0-92842ea40ad8"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"ac952503582830ccc","tool_use_id":"toolu_01J4ny8RFKt7ajdut1mfrG1Y","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Find workflow view UI code","usage":{"total_tokens":49176,"tool_uses":14,"duration_ms":34223},"uuid":"d177a9ba-48d3-4474-a703-b9dc7fd88c43","session_id":"735f5643-f2ce-48be-a0fe-61ddf324c836"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J4ny8RFKt7ajdut1mfrG1Y","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report of my findings:\n\n## Summary of Workflow View Implementation\n\nI found the complete workflow view implementation in the Cloche project. Here's what I discovered:\n\n### 1. **Web Handler** \nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe main handlers involved:\n- **`handleAPIWorkflows()`** (lines 1058-1132): Returns JSON list of all workflows in a project with their steps, wires, and step definitions\n- **`handleAPIStepContent()`** (lines 1134-1199): **This is the key endpoint that fetches file contents for steps**\n\nThe HTTP routes are:\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` - Lists all workflows\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` - **Fetches step file content**\n\n### 2. **The File Content Loading Issue**\n\nIn `handleAPIStepContent()` (lines 1134-1199), the handler:\n1. Resolves the project directory\n2. Finds the workflow by name\n3. Gets the step definition\n4. Attempts to read file contents based on step config keys:\n   - `prompt` key: reads from `filepath.Join(dir, prompt)` \n   - `command` key: returns the command string directly\n   - `script` key: reads from `filepath.Join(dir, script)`\n\n**The endpoint IS implemented and working**. It successfully loads prompt/script file contents when called.\n\n### 3. **Frontend Display** \nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\nThe JavaScript code:\n- **Lines 142-161**: `loadWorkflows()` fetches workflow data via `/api/projects/{label}/workflows`\n  - Returns step definitions WITH filenames in config keys (`prompt`, `script`, `command`)\n  - **Displays these filenames in the drawer** (line 264)\n\n- **Lines 251-284**: `openDrawer()` function:\n  - Shows step metadata and config keys (including prompt/script filenames) immediately\n  - **Then makes an async fetch** to `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` (line 274)\n  - Loads file contents into the drawer asynchronously (lines 275-283)\n\n### 4. **Visual Components**\n\n**CSS Styling** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`):\n- Lines 491-549: `.drawer` styling for the side panel\n- Lines 457-489: DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) SVG styling for workflow visualization\n- Lines 434-455: Tab styling for multiple workflow selection\n\n**HTML Template** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`):\n- Lines 31-47: Workflow view panels (tabs, DAG canvas, drawer)\n- Lines 163-249: DAG rendering function - draws steps as nodes with icons\n  - Agent steps show \"🤖\" emoji\n  - Script steps show \"📄\" emoji\n  - Steps are clickable and trigger `openDrawer()`\n\n### 5. **Data Flow**\n\n```\nProject Detail Page\n├── loadWorkflows()\n│   └── GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n│       └── Returns: [{name, steps: [{name, type, config: {prompt, script, command}}], wires, entry_step}]\n│           └── displayWorkflowSteps as DAG visualization\n└── openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)\n    ├── Display step metadata from in-memory workflowsData (instant)\n    │   └── Shows config keys like \"prompt: .cloche/prompts/fix.md\"\n    └── fetch /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n        └── GET handler reads file and returns content\n            └── Display content in pre tag within drawer\n```\n\n### **Key Files**\n\n1. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** - HTTP handlers for workflows and step content\n2. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`** - Frontend UI and JavaScript for workflow DAG and drawer\n3. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`** - Styling for drawer panel and DAG visualization\n4. **`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`** - Workflow and Step domain models\n\n### **Route Handlers Summary**\n\n| Route | Method | Handler | Purpose |\n|-------|--------|---------|---------|\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows` | GET | `handleAPIWorkflows` | List all workflows with step definitions |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` | GET | `handleAPIStepContent` | Load prompt/script file contents for a specific step |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac952503582830ccc (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 50275\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 34228</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"735f5643-f2ce-48be-a0fe-61ddf324c836","uuid":"6c864cc4-03ec-4c13-be61-4204349d82f4","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find code related to the \"workflow view\" in a project page where clicking on steps shows prompt/script filenames but doesn't load file contents. This is a Go project called \"Cloche\". \n\nLook for:\n1. Any web UI / frontend code (HTML templates, JavaScript, handlers)\n2. HTTP handlers related to project pages or workflow views\n3. Code that renders workflow steps and their associated prompt/script files\n4. Any API endpoints that serve file contents for workflow steps\n\nSearch thoroughly across the codebase - check cmd/, internal/, and any web/static/template directories. Look for patterns like \"workflow\", \"step\", \"prompt\", \"project page\", \"file content\", \"load file\", template files, etc.","agentId":"ac952503582830ccc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive report of my findings:\n\n## Summary of Workflow View Implementation\n\nI found the complete workflow view implementation in the Cloche project. Here's what I discovered:\n\n### 1. **Web Handler** \nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe main handlers involved:\n- **`handleAPIWorkflows()`** (lines 1058-1132): Returns JSON list of all workflows in a project with their steps, wires, and step definitions\n- **`handleAPIStepContent()`** (lines 1134-1199): **This is the key endpoint that fetches file contents for steps**\n\nThe HTTP routes are:\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` - Lists all workflows\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` - **Fetches step file content**\n\n### 2. **The File Content Loading Issue**\n\nIn `handleAPIStepContent()` (lines 1134-1199), the handler:\n1. Resolves the project directory\n2. Finds the workflow by name\n3. Gets the step definition\n4. Attempts to read file contents based on step config keys:\n   - `prompt` key: reads from `filepath.Join(dir, prompt)` \n   - `command` key: returns the command string directly\n   - `script` key: reads from `filepath.Join(dir, script)`\n\n**The endpoint IS implemented and working**. It successfully loads prompt/script file contents when called.\n\n### 3. **Frontend Display** \nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\nThe JavaScript code:\n- **Lines 142-161**: `loadWorkflows()` fetches workflow data via `/api/projects/{label}/workflows`\n  - Returns step definitions WITH filenames in config keys (`prompt`, `script`, `command`)\n  - **Displays these filenames in the drawer** (line 264)\n\n- **Lines 251-284**: `openDrawer()` function:\n  - Shows step metadata and config keys (including prompt/script filenames) immediately\n  - **Then makes an async fetch** to `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` (line 274)\n  - Loads file contents into the drawer asynchronously (lines 275-283)\n\n### 4. **Visual Components**\n\n**CSS Styling** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`):\n- Lines 491-549: `.drawer` styling for the side panel\n- Lines 457-489: DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) SVG styling for workflow visualization\n- Lines 434-455: Tab styling for multiple workflow selection\n\n**HTML Template** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`):\n- Lines 31-47: Workflow view panels (tabs, DAG canvas, drawer)\n- Lines 163-249: DAG rendering function - draws steps as nodes with icons\n  - Agent steps show \"🤖\" emoji\n  - Script steps show \"📄\" emoji\n  - Steps are clickable and trigger `openDrawer()`\n\n### 5. **Data Flow**\n\n```\nProject Detail Page\n├── loadWorkflows()\n│   └── GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n│       └── Returns: [{name, steps: [{name, type, config: {prompt, script, command}}], wires, entry_step}]\n│           └── displayWorkflowSteps as DAG visualization\n└── openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)\n    ├── Display step metadata from in-memory workflowsData (instant)\n    │   └── Shows config keys like \"prompt: .cloche/prompts/fix.md\"\n    └── fetch /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n        └── GET handler reads file and returns content\n            └── Display content in pre tag within drawer\n```\n\n### **Key Files**\n\n1. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** - HTTP handlers for workflows and step content\n2. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`** - Frontend UI and JavaScript for workflow DAG and drawer\n3. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`** - Styling for drawer panel and DAG visualization\n4. **`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`** - Workflow and Step domain models\n\n### **Route Handlers Summary**\n\n| Route | Method | Handler | Purpose |\n|-------|--------|---------|---------|\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows` | GET | `handleAPIWorkflows` | List all workflows with step definitions |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` | GET | `handleAPIStepContent` | Load prompt/script file contents for a specific step |"}],"totalDurationMs":34228,"totalTokens":50275,"totalToolUseCount":14,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":951,"cache_read_input_tokens":48170,"output_tokens":1154,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":951},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
